1.Hola – “Hello”
This is the simplest way to say “hello” in Spanish.
It’s a friendly, greeting that can be used in pretty much any situation.

2.Qué tal? – “How are you?”
Qué tal is the most commonly used phrase to say How are you.

3.Qué pasa? – “What’s up?”
Qué pasa is the more informal way of asking how it's going.
If you want a more informal, casual way of greeting you can say Qué pasa?

4.Cómo te va? – “How’re you doing?”
5.Bien – “Good”
6.Muy bien – “Very good”
Así así – “So-so”
No tan bien – “Not so good”